about.description: Find the root of a git repo
about.summary: Find the root of a git repo

name: git_root
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "git_root" %}
{% set version = "0.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/jtilly/{{ name }}/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 34d7edee2413d8c80700b2273ea75bb58162e65343e07e5b974742be5681003a

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - git_root

about:
  home: https://github.com/jtilly/git_root
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Find the root of a git repo'
  description: 'Find the root of a git repo'
  dev_url: https://github.com/jtilly/git_root

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jtilly
